(97, 1, '2014-04-10 12:30:05', '2014-04-10 12:30:05', 'Acorn presently has two live funds and a third is planned for later in 2014. The Acorn Funds are structured as en commandite limited partnerships. Acorn therefor accepts unlimited liability on the investments made by the partnership whilst the other partners (the Limited Partner investors) assume limited liability. This ensures exclusivity and a close relationship with our investors.\r\n\r\nACORN GENERAL FUND ONE\r\nAcorn General Fund One had a Southern-Africa geographic focus and invested in small- to mid-cap opportunities. It was fully invested within 21 months of first close and is not open for further investment. After two successful exits the remaining investments are being actively managed to ensure long-term growth.\r\n\r\nACORN VENTURE TECHNOLOGY\r\nAcorn Venture Technology Fund looked for opportunities in the technology space in Southern Africa. The fund is closed to new investors and following a successful exit houses one remaining investment.\r\n\r\nACORN SME FUND TWO\r\nAcorn is planning to raise a third fund during the second half of 2014. The fund will invest throughout Sub-Saharan Africa across a range of industries. We are looking to target a more diverse investor base to include institutional investors alongside our existing group of high net-worth individuals.\r\n\r\nPlease contact us for further information regarding Acorn SME Fund Two.', 'LLP Funds', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-10 12:30:05', '2014-04-10 12:30:05', '', 70, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(98, 1, '2014-04-10 12:31:36', '2014-04-10 12:31:36', 'Acorn incorporated an investment holding company called Acorn Agri (Pty) Ltd in February 2014. Acorn Private Equity has a long-term management agreement in place with Acorn Agri (Pty) Ltd and is also a significant shareholder in the cpmpany.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this investment company is to participate in the consolidation and growth in the Southern African agri sector. This will be achieved by acquiring significant stakes in strategic agri and food businesses to create a diversified portfolio by geography, commodity and type. By acquiring best of breed businesses in critical sectors the investment company will create pockets of excellence ensuring regional food security and sustainable returns.\r\n\r\nAcorn Agri (Pty) Ltd has already raised R300 million from both individual and institutional investors for investment purposes.\r\n\r\nIn February 2014 Acorn Agri (Pty) Ltd acquired a 23% stake in Overberg Agri (Pty) Ltd, a diversified regional agri business, for R200 million. Further acquisitions are planned for the near future, with some negotiations at an advanced stage.\r\n\r\nAcorn Agri (Pty) Ltd is looking to raise further capital for future investments. Interested investors are welcome to contact us.\r\n\r\nFor more information please visit the Acorn Agri webpage.', 'Investment Company', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '72-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-10 12:31:36', '2014-04-10 12:31:36', '', 72, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/72-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(99, 1, '2014-04-24 12:34:07', '2014-04-24 10:34:07', 'Investment advisory is an important part of Acorn’s activities. Acorn´s principals have extensive experience in corporate finance transactions, having completed a number of stock market listings, delistings, mergers and buyouts. This experience enables our Team to provide clients with innovative ideas and sound advice.\n\nAcorn has never actively marketed itself as an advisor, rather we rely on our extensive network and reputation in the market to bring clients to us. The advisory activities create new or strengthen existing relationships that help grow our network and often lead to new investment opportunities.\n\nBelow is a list of advisory deals that Acorn has lead since 2011:\n<table style="width: 600px;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Year</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Transacting Parties</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Type of Transaction</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Value (Rands million)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2013</td>\n<td>Tuinroete Agri &amp; KLK Landbou</td>\n<td>Share Acquisition</td>\n<td>180</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2013</td>\n<td>P&amp;B Limeworks &amp; Empolweni Trust</td>\n<td>BBBEE Minority acquisition</td>\n<td>20</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2012</td>\n<td>Overberg Agri &amp; Moorreesburgse\nKoringboere</td>\n<td>Share Acquisition</td>\n<td>927</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2012</td>\n<td>Pioneer Food Group &amp; Coronation\nFund Managers</td>\n<td>Placement of Shares</td>\n<td>500</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2011</td>\n<td>Loch Duart &amp; Aquapemba</td>\n<td>Share Acquisition</td>\n<td>20</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;', 'Investment Advisory', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '74-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-24 12:34:07', '2014-04-24 10:34:07', '', 74, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/74-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(100, 1, '2014-04-10 12:34:40', '2014-04-10 12:34:40', 'Investment advisory is an important part of Acorn’s activities. Acorn´s principals have extensive experience in corporate finance transactions having completed a number of stock market listings, delistings, mergers and buyouts. This experience enables our Team to provide clients with innovative ideas and sound advice.\r\n\r\nAcorn has never actively marketed itself as an advisor, rather we rely on our extensive network and reputation in the market to bring clients to us. The advisory activities create new or strengthen existing relationships that help grow our network and often lead to new investment opportunities.\r\n\r\nBelow is a list of advisory deals that Acorn has lead since 2011:\r\n\r\n//INSERT TABLE HERE', 'Investment Advisory', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '74-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-10 12:34:40', '2014-04-10 12:34:40', '', 74, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/74-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(101, 1, '2014-04-10 12:36:17', '2014-04-10 12:36:17', '<strong>Current Investments</strong>\r\n\r\n//INSERT TABLE HERE\r\n\r\n<strong>Realised Investments</strong>\r\n\r\n//INSERT TABLE HERE', 'Portfolio', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '76-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-10 12:36:17', '2014-04-10 12:36:17', '', 76, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/76-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(102, 1, '2014-04-10 12:38:35', '2014-04-10 12:38:35', 'Acorn’s team members have historically applied specific business principles in private equity investments that have contributed to exceptional returns and consistent outperformance of most of their competitors. Acorn will apply similar principles to the investments of Acorn SME Fund 2.\n\nThese principles include:\n<ul>\n	<li>Allowing management teams within Portfolio Companies to acquire shareholding in the companies they manage. This better aligns management to the goals of all the shareholders and also serves as the strongest motivation for management to improve their business’s performance in the medium to long-term.</li>\n	<li>Focusing on growing and profitable sectors.</li>\n	<li>Investing in profitable enterprises that are operating in growth sectors in Southern Africa allows for substantial organic growth without the need to apply aggressive restructuring or cost-cutting policies to the current operations</li>\n	<li>Ensuring that strong, dynamic and innovative managers run the daily operations of the Portfolio Companies.</li>\n	<li>Ensuring that a strong and proactive Board of Directors is able to provide insight and guidance to the managers. • Focusing on businesses with significant scalability. • Being price sensitive and not entering into a transaction if the pricing isn´t right. This all allows for significant growth and exceptional returns for investors.</li>\n</ul>', 'Investment Strategy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '80-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-10 12:38:35', '2014-04-10 12:38:35', '', 80, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/80-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(103, 1, '2014-04-10 12:39:09', '2014-04-10 12:39:09', 'Acorn’s team members have historically applied specific business principles in private equity investments that have contributed to exceptional returns and consistent outperformance of most of their competitors. Acorn will apply similar principles to the investments of Acorn SME Fund 2.\r\n\r\nThese principles include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Allowing management teams within Portfolio Companies to acquire shareholding in the companies they manage. This better aligns management to the goals of all the shareholders and also serves as the strongest motivation for management to improve their business’s performance in the medium to long-term.</li>\r\n	<li>Focusing on growing and profitable sectors.</li>\r\n	<li>Investing in profitable enterprises that are operating in growth sectors in Southern Africa allows for substantial organic growth without the need to apply aggressive restructuring or cost-cutting policies to the current operations</li>\r\n	<li>Ensuring that strong, dynamic and innovative managers run the daily operations of the Portfolio Companies.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensuring that a strong and proactive Board of Directors is able to provide insight and guidance to the managers.</li>\r\n	<li>Focusing on businesses with significant scalability.</li>\r\n	<li>Being price sensitive and not entering into a transaction if the pricing isn´t right.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis all allows for significant growth and exceptional returns for investors.', 'Investment Strategy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '80-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-10 12:39:09', '2014-04-10 12:39:09', '', 80, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/80-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(104, 1, '2014-04-10 12:41:46', '2014-04-10 12:41:46', '<strong>ACORN SME FUND TWO: </strong>\n\n<strong>Targeted Fund Size</strong>\nMinimum first close R300m, targeted fund size R500m, maximum fund size capped at R750m.\n\n<strong>Targeted Companies</strong>\nThe fund invests in established family-owned or entrepreneurial businesses with an enterprise value of R50m - R200m and pre-tax profit of R10m - R50m at the time of investment.\n\n<strong>Investment Size</strong>\nThe targeted investment size per transaction is R30m - R80m.\n\n<strong>Stage of Investment</strong>\nCompanies in the growth and expansion stage will be considered. No investment in early stage or start-up companies will be made.\n\n<strong>Industries</strong>\nThe fund will focus on basic consumer goods and services, such as investments in food production and processing, utilities, healthcare, waste management, infrastructure development and engineering and aims to preclude capital-intensive industries such as primary agriculture, mining and real estate.\n\n<strong>Geography</strong>\nTarget is 50% South Africa, 30% Southern Africa (excluding RSA), and 20% discretionary Sub-Saharan Africa.\n\n<strong>Qualitative Considerations</strong>\nGiven Acorn´s emphasis on partnership with management we only consider investments where we believe this partnership is likely to succeed. This includes partnering with competent and honest management teams and ensuring that they have equity ownership in their respective companies. Furthermore, our investee companies must have easily understandable business models, robust financial health and a clear competitive advantage. Growth prospects must be present in investee companies as well as the ability to create jobs and positively impact the communities and environment in which they operate.', 'Investment Criteria', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '78-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-10 12:41:46', '2014-04-10 12:41:46', '', 78, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/78-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(105, 1, '2014-04-10 12:41:54', '2014-04-10 12:41:54', '<strong>ACORN SME FUND TWO: </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Targeted Fund Size</strong>\r\nMinimum first close R300m, targeted fund size R500m, maximum fund size capped at R750m.\r\n\r\n<strong>Targeted Companies</strong>\r\nThe fund invests in established family-owned or entrepreneurial businesses with an enterprise value of R50m - R200m and pre-tax profit of R10m - R50m at the time of investment.\r\n\r\n<strong>Investment Size</strong>\r\nThe targeted investment size per transaction is R30m - R80m.\r\n\r\n<strong>Stage of Investment</strong>\r\nCompanies in the growth and expansion stage will be considered. No investment in early stage or start-up companies will be made.\r\n\r\n<strong>Industries</strong>\r\nThe fund will focus on basic consumer goods and services, such as investments in food production and processing, utilities, healthcare, waste management, infrastructure development and engineering and aims to preclude capital-intensive industries such as primary agriculture, mining and real estate.\r\n\r\n<strong>Geography</strong>\r\nTarget is 50% South Africa, 30% Southern Africa (excluding RSA), and 20% discretionary Sub-Saharan Africa.\r\n\r\n<strong>Qualitative Considerations</strong>\r\nGiven Acorn´s emphasis on partnership with management we only consider investments where we believe this partnership is likely to succeed. This includes partnering with competent and honest management teams and ensuring that they have equity ownership in their respective companies. Furthermore, our investee companies must have easily understandable business models, robust financial health and a clear competitive advantage. Growth prospects must be present in investee companies as well as the ability to create jobs and positively impact the communities and environment in which they operate.', 'Investment Criteria', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '78-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-10 12:41:54', '2014-04-10 12:41:54', '', 78, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/78-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(106, 1, '2014-04-10 12:44:46', '2014-04-10 12:44:46', 'At the core of the Acorn Equity investment ethos is a commitment to delivering returns to our investors and contributing to the generation of long-term sustainable value for other stakeholders through the adoption of responsible investment practises focussed on environmental, social and governance issues. Integral to the investment decision-making and portfolio management processes, and to the best of their ability, the Acorn Equity team is specifically committed to:\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Human rights</strong>\nRespect the protection of international human rights and avoid complicity in human rights violations.</li>\n	<li><strong>Labour development and rights</strong>\nPromote sound labour development and rights practices including considering employee working conditions, supporting the abolishment of child labour, promoting employees’ right to collective bargaining, eliminating forced labour, avoidance of employment discrimination and compliance with applicable labour laws.</li>\n	<li><strong>The environment</strong>\nTake a cautious and responsible approach to the environment, aiming to promote an appropriate level of environmental awareness and sound environmental practices in portfolio companies including compliance with current environmental laws.</li>\n	<li><strong>Anti-corruption</strong>\nAvoidance of corruption in all its forms and to subscribe to ethical behaviour that is captured in our membership to Unashamedly Ethical.</li>\n	<li><strong>Robust corporate governance</strong>\nSeek to use governance structures that provide appropriate levels of oversight in the areas of audit, risk management and potential conflicts of interest and to implement compensation and other policies that align the interests of owners and management.</li>\n</ol>\nAcorn Private Equity will provide timely information and maintain an open and transparent dialogue with investors on the matters addressed herein.', 'ESG', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-10 12:44:46', '2014-04-10 12:44:46', '', 11, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn/11-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
